  <para>
    <link linkend="RegisteredClass-Refine">Refining</link> &skel;
    elements with <varname>degree</varname> set to
    <classname>Bisection</classname> divides each marked edge into two
    segments.
  </para>
  <para>
    The <varname>rule_set</varname> parameter determines how the
    interior of each element is subdivided, given the number of
    subdivisions on each edge.  The complete set of refinement rules
    for <classname>Bisection</classname> can be found in <xref
    linkend='Table:refine_rule_quad'/> and <xref
    linkend='Table:refine_rule_tri'/>.
  </para>

  <para>
    <xref linkend='Figure-bi_conservative'/> shows a &skel; refined by
    the <userinput>conservative</userinput> bisection rule set, which
    preserves the topology of the elements (quadrilaterals beget
    quadrilaterals and triangles beget triangles).  The original
    unrefined &skel; is shown in <xref linkend="Figure-refine0"/>, and
    the refined elements are indicated with heavy black edges.

    <figure id="Figure-bi_conservative">
      <title>Bisected Elements - Conservative</title>
      <mediaobject>
	<imageobject>
	  <imagedata format="PNG" fileref="FIGURES/refinement/bi_conservative.png"></imagedata>
	</imageobject>
	<imageobject>
	  <imagedata format="EPS" fileref="FIGURES/refinement/bi_conservative.eps"></imagedata>
	</imageobject>
	<caption>
	  <para>
	    The topology of the elements has been preserved.
	  </para>
	</caption>
      </mediaobject>
    </figure>
  </para>

  <para>
    The <emphasis>liberal</emphasis> <classname>Bisection</classname>
    rule set is presented in <xref linkend='Figure-bi_liberal'/>. As
    expected. the &skel; features a mixture of triangles and
    quadrilaterals -- note that its original &skel; contained only
    quadrilaterals.

    <figure id="Figure-bi_liberal">
      <title>Bisected Elements - Liberal</title>
      <mediaobject>
	<imageobject>
	  <imagedata format="PNG" fileref="FIGURES/refinement/refine2.png"></imagedata>
	</imageobject>
	<imageobject>
	  <imagedata format="EPS" fileref="FIGURES/refinement/refine2.eps"></imagedata>
	</imageobject>
	<caption>
	  <para>
	    Triangles and Quadrilaterals exisiting together peacefully.
	  </para>
	</caption>
      </mediaobject>
    </figure>
  </para>


